The nine foot (three-metre) reptile was one of the larger reptiles that lived before dinosaurs roamed the planet.

‘The full name is actually Nundasuchus songeaensis,' Sterling Nesbitt, an assistant professor of geological sciences at Virginia Tech explained.

The name means ‘predator crocodile’ with ‘unda’ meaning predator in Swahili and ‘suchus’ a reference to a crocodile in Greek. 

